ğŸ¤– MemeChatBot

MemeChatBot is a lightweight Discord bot built with Python and discord.py.
It listens to messages in a server and responds to simple commands, serving as a beginner-friendly project to learn how Discord bots work, including events, intents, and asynchronous programming.

This project was created as a hands-on learning exercise and can be easily extended with new commands, memes, moderation tools, or external API integrations.

ğŸš€ Features

Connects to Discord using a bot token

Listens to messages in real time

Responds to simple commands (e.g. $hello)

Clean and minimal structure for easy understanding

ğŸ› ï¸ Technologies Used

Python

discord.py

Git & GitHub

ğŸ“¦ Installation

Clone the repository:

git clone https://github.com/yourusername/MemeChatBot.git


Navigate to the project folder:

cd MemeChatBot


Install dependencies:

pip install discord.py

ğŸ”‘ Configuration

Create a Discord application and bot at
https://discord.com/developers/applications

Copy your Bot Token

Set the token as an environment variable:

Windows (PowerShell):

setx DISCORD_TOKEN "your_token_here"


Update the code to use the environment variable if needed.

âš ï¸ Never share or commit your bot token.

â–¶ï¸ Usage

Run the bot with:

python bot.py


In your Discord server, type:

$hello


The bot will respond with:

Hello World!

ğŸ“Œ Notes

The bot token is not included for security reasons

This project is intended for educational purposes

Works as a foundation for more advanced Discord bots

